- 'latest available financial years' refers to the most recent year for which financial data is available for each company; 
- 'highest revenues' means the companies are ordered by their total revenue in descending order, so the companies with the largest revenues are at the top of the list; 
- 'maximum market shares' and 'largest market regions' are calculated based on the market share and region data available for each company across different markets.
